American Assets Investment Management Has Boosted Its Glaxosmithkline Plc (GSK) Holding; Shorts at Madrigal Pharmaceuticals (MDGL) Lowered By 6.09%

July 25, 2017 - By Marguerite Chambers

 Madrigal Pharmaceuticals Incorporated (NASDAQ:MDGL) had a decrease of 6.09% in short interest. MDGL’s SI was 50,900 shares in July as released by FINRA. Its down 6.09% from 54,200 shares previously. With 21,900 avg volume, 2 days are for Madrigal Pharmaceuticals Incorporated (NASDAQ:MDGL)’s short sellers to cover MDGL’s short positions. The SI to Madrigal Pharmaceuticals Incorporated’s float is 1.06%. It closed at $15.55 lastly. It is down 0.00% since July 25, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.
American Assets Investment Management Llc increased Glaxosmithkline Plc (GSK) stake by 50% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. American Assets Investment Management Llc acquired 10,000 shares as Glaxosmithkline Plc (GSK)’s stock rose 5.47%. The American Assets Investment Management Llc holds 30,000 shares with $1.16 million value, up from 20,000 last quarter. Glaxosmithkline Plc now has $100.95 billion valuation. The stock declined 0.33% or $0.14 reaching $42.1 on the news. About 71,768 shares traded. GlaxoSmithKline plc (ADR) (NYSE:GSK) has risen 4.26% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 12.44% the S&P500.







Madrigal Pharmaceuticals, Inc., formerly Synta Pharmaceuticals Corp., is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company. The company has market cap of $188.72 million. The Firm focuses on the development and commercialization of therapeutic candidates for the treatment of cardiovascular-metabolic diseases and nonalcoholic steatohepatitis . It has a 2.48 P/E ratio. The Company’s lead product, MGL-3196, is a Phase II-ready once-daily, oral, liver-directed selective thyroid hormone receptor-b (THR-b) agonist for the treatment of NASH, and heterozygous and homozygous familial hypercholesterolemia (FH).
Among 14 analysts covering GlaxoSmithKline (NYSE:GSK), 7 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 7 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. GlaxoSmithKline had 21 analyst reports since September 8, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock has “Buy” rating by Bank of America on Wednesday, December 9. The rating was upgraded by BNP Paribas on Wednesday, April 5 to “Neutral”. Bryan Garnier & Cie upgraded GlaxoSmithKline plc (ADR) (NYSE:GSK) on Wednesday, January 27 to “Buy” rating. The stock of GlaxoSmithKline plc (ADR) (NYSE:GSK) earned “Neutral” rating by Bank of America on Tuesday, September 8. The company was maintained on Monday, December 7 by Argus Research. JP Morgan maintained the stock with “Neutral” rating in Wednesday, April 26 report. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Friday, May 26 by Berenberg. The rating was initiated by Piperjaffray on Friday, September 23 with “Overweight”. The rating was upgraded by JP Morgan on Monday, October 12 to “Neutral”. On Wednesday, September 14 the stock rating was downgraded by BNP Paribas to “Underperform”.
American Assets Investment Management Llc decreased Goldman Sachs Group Inc (NYSE:GS) stake by 10,060 shares to 36,360 valued at $8.71M in 2016Q4. It also reduced Wynn Resorts Ltd (NASDAQ:WYNN) stake by 5,000 shares and now owns 3,000 shares. Annaly Cap Mgmt Inc (NYSE:NLY) was reduced too. 


