American Assets Investment Management LLC Reduces Stake in Bank of America Corporation (NYSE:BAC)

					Posted by Rex Bailey on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












American Assets Investment Management LLC decreased its position in  Bank of America Corporation (NYSE:BAC) by 42.2% during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 90,000 shares of the financial services provider’s stock after selling 65,770 shares during the period. American Assets Investment Management LLC’s holdings in Bank of America Corporation were worth $2,123,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other hedge funds also recently bought and sold shares of BAC. Gardner Lewis Asset Management L P boosted its stake in  Bank of America Corporation by 23.0% in the fourth quarter. Gardner Lewis Asset Management L P now owns 619,684 shares of the financial services provider’s stock worth $13,695,000 after buying an additional 115,715 shares in the last quarter.  Guardian Capital Advisors LP boosted its stake in  Bank of America Corporation by 4.0% in the fourth quarter. Guardian Capital Advisors LP now owns 13,391 shares of the financial services provider’s stock worth $304,000 after buying an additional 513 shares in the last quarter.  Guardian Capital LP acquired a new position in  Bank of America Corporation during the fourth quarter worth approximately $21,875,000.  Sandhill Capital Partners LLC raised its position in  Bank of America Corporation by 4.1% in the fourth quarter. Sandhill Capital Partners LLC now owns 862,984 shares of the financial services provider’s stock worth $19,072,000 after buying an additional 34,227 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Public Sector Pension Investment Board raised its position in  Bank of America Corporation by 313.4% in the fourth quarter. Public Sector Pension Investment Board now owns 9,459,219 shares of the financial services provider’s stock worth $209,049,000 after buying an additional 7,170,800 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors own  65.89% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Bank of America Corporation alerts:



Shares of Bank of America Corporation (NYSE BAC) opened at 23.80 on Friday. Bank of America Corporation has a 52-week low of $14.09 and a 52-week high of $25.80. The company’s 50-day moving average is $23.71 and its 200 day moving average is $23.61. The firm has a market capitalization of $250.29 billion, a P/E ratio of 14.65 and a beta of 1.27. 




Bank of America Corporation (NYSE:BAC) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, July 18th. The financial services provider reported $0.46 EPS for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.43 by $0.03. Bank of America Corporation had a net margin of 20.28% and a return on equity of 8.11%. The business had revenue of $22.80 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $21.84 billion. During the same period last year, the business earned $0.41 earnings per share. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 7.1% on a year-over-year basis.  Analysts expect that  Bank of America Corporation will post $1.81 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
Bank of America Corporation declared that its Board of Directors has initiated a stock repurchase program on Wednesday, June 28th that permits the company to repurchase $12.00 billion in  outstanding  shares. This repurchase authorization permits the financial services provider to reacquire up to 4.8% of its stock  through open market purchases. Stock  repurchase programs are typically a sign that the company’s board believes its shares are undervalued. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Friday, June 30th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 2nd were given a dividend of $0.075 per share. This represents a $0.30 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.26%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, May 31st. Bank of America Corporation’s payout ratio is currently 17.86%. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: “American Assets Investment Management LLC Reduces Stake in Bank of America Corporation (NYSE:BAC)” was originally  posted by Week Herald and is the property of of Week Herald. If you are reading this article on another domain, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of United States and international copyright law. The legal version of this article can be accessed at https://weekherald.com/2017/07/23/american-assets-investment-management-llc-reduces-stake-in-bank-of-america-corporation-nysebac.html. 
A number of equities analysts recently commented on the stock. Instinet  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and set a $27.00 price target on shares of Bank of America Corporation in a research report on Saturday. Oppenheimer Holdings, Inc.  reaffirmed an “outperform” rating and set a $30.00 price target (up from $29.00) on shares of Bank of America Corporation in a research report on Friday. UBS AG  reaffirmed a “neutral” rating and set a $26.00 price target on shares of Bank of America Corporation in a research report on Friday. Royal Bank Of Canada  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and set a $26.00 price target on shares of Bank of America Corporation in a research report on Thursday. Finally, BidaskClub lowered shares of Bank of America Corporation from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Wednesday. One equities research analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating, twelve have given a hold rating, twenty-three have assigned  a buy rating and two have given a strong buy rating to the company’s stock. The stock presently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $23.74.
In other news, Director Thomas D. Woods bought 25,000 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Thursday, April 27th. The shares were purchased at an average price of $23.81 per share, for a total transaction of $595,250.00. Following the completion of the acquisition, the director now owns 40,830 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $972,162.30. The transaction was disclosed in a legal filing with the SEC, which is accessible through this link. 0.18% of the stock is owned by company insiders. 
Bank of America Corporation Company Profile
Bank of America Corporation is a bank holding company and a financial holding company. The Company is a financial institution, serving individual consumers and others with a range of banking, investing, asset management and other financial and risk management products and services. The Company, through its banking and various non-bank subsidiaries, throughout the United States and in international markets, provides a range of banking and non-bank financial services and products through four business segments: Consumer Banking, which comprises Deposits and Consumer Lending; Global Wealth & Investment Management, which consists of two primary businesses: Merrill Lynch Global Wealth Management and U.S.
